snippet.textDisplay:
As a recovering opiate addict/drug addict in general, I personally thank you for spreading the message of how using drugs such as Xanax are NOT cool or good.
Juice’s passing will hopefully be the final straw for the hip hop/rap/pop community and make them want to stop glorifying drug use. More than half of the artists who rap about drugs and taking them don’t even do them in the first place!
The opiate epidemic in our county especially is HORRENDOUS and DESPICABLE and has been out of control for decades! Hundreds of thousands, if not millions, of people of all ages are dying, overdosing & struggling with opiates every minute of everyday. I’ve lost a lot of rehab buddies of mine to overdosing. I want to create myself a platform to tell my story and help those still struggling with addiction today.
If you’d be so kind and/or interested in helping me reach a larger audience, please respond to this comment of mine. If you do, I’ll send you my email and/or phone number. I’m 100% serious about this as if it weren’t for the support and love from my doctors, friends and family I wouldn’t be here typing you this comment. I’d greatly appreciate a response regardless of your decision. My generation as well as yours are dropping like flies and will continue to drop if we keep letting this shit slide. I’m only 27 and I can’t imagine how bad it’ll get in 10 years if we don’t start to help this epidemic.
✨💛🙏💛✨
